The All Progressives Congress (APC) has said it has not concluded on plans regarding the party primaries ahead of the 2023 elections. The National Publicity Secretary of the party, Mr. Felix Morka stated this Wednesday in Abuja while briefing journalists after the meeting of the National Working Committee (NWC) of the party. The party spokesperson insisted that the ruling party had not put out any information into the public space about the schedule of activities for its primaries. Morka, however, confirmed that the leadership had the discussion and talks were still in progress. He said while the schedule of activities of the party was discussed amongst other issues, no decision had been made in that regard. His words: “Today, the 6th of April, 2022, the NWC of the APC met and we just rose from that meeting. Amongst other topics covered was as you properly expected, we discussed the programme for our party’s primaries looking at the schedule of activities that is to come. “But I am not able to give you the rundown of the details of that schedule because that is still in discussion. We are yet to conclude on a definite plan or timetable or schedule for our primaries. “But I can confirm that we did have that conversation today. At least we did begin that conversation today but we have not concluded and we have not made any decision.” He said as soon as the details are concluded, the general public would be informed about it.